comments: Gobert (UTA) briefly places his arm on Plumlee (CHA) in the post.
Washington (CHA) makes marginal contact with O'Neale (UTA) as he is rolling towards the rim.
Ball (CHA) makes marginal contact with O'Neale (UTA) after he has returned to the floor from his jump shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) makes marginal contact with O'Neale (UTA) as he is rolling towards the rim.
Washington (CHA) is established in Conley's (UTA) path and makes marginal contact during the screen attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) gathers and legally takes two steps before passing the ball.
Rozier (CHA) makes marginal body contact with Mitchell (UTA) during his drive towards the rim.
Ball (CHA) initiates arm contact with Gobert (UTA) before making contact with the ball that affects his ability to control the pass.
Washington (CHA) briefly places two hands on Gobert (UTA) during the screen attempt before disengaging.
Martin (CHA) initiates marginal contact with Mitchell (UTA) that he is able to move through during his driving shot attempt.
Mitchell (UTA) extends his leg but avoids initiating contact with Martin (CHA) during his driving shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) makes marginal body contact with O'Neale (UTA) as he is rolling towards the rim.
Clarkson (UTA) briefly places his arm on Bridges' (CHA) front at the start of his drive, the contact is marginal and did not affect Bridges' SQBR.
Gobert (UTA) delivers contact to Bridges' (CHA) body during his shot attempt.
Bridges (CHA) briefly places his arm on Mitchell's (UTA) body as he makes his move towards the rim.
Bridges' (CHA) foot makes marginal contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm while contesting the shot attempt.
Gobert (UTA) and Plumlee (CHA) make incidental arm contact with each other reaching for the rebound.
Clarkson (UTA) commits a take foul against Rozier (CHA).
Martin (CHA) and Clarkson (UTA) mutually engage and disengage during the screen attempt.
O'Neale (UTA) commits a take foul against Bridges (CHA).
Mitchell (UTA) and Martin (CHA) mutually engage and disengage as they both fight for the rebound.
